title: ICE with inherent associated type: Type parameter out of range when substituting

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: A-associated-items
labels.description: Area: Associated items such as associated types and consts.

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-nightly
labels.description: This issue requires a nightly compiler in some way.

body:
### Code ```rust #![feature(inherent_associated_types)] #![allow(incomplete_features)] struct S(T); impl S { type P = T; } fn main() { type A = S<()>::P; let _: A = (); } ``` #### Output ``` error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_middle/src/ty/subst.rs:726:9: type parameter `T/#0` (T/0) out of range when substituting, substs=[] thread 'rustc' panicked at 'Box', /rustc/85f4f41deb1557ca8ab228319d33003dd2f20f45/compiler/rustc_errors/src/lib.rs:1551:9 ```
